tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Finished 147th at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Played in 10 events on the Swing Thought Tour.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: In high school, led Deerfield-Windsor Academy to two state championships, including an undefeated season in 2008. Was Southeastern Conference first team and team captain his final two years at the University of Georgia. Notched his only career college victory, at the Old Dominion/Outerbanks Collegiate as a junior.
tourBios.personal: Favorite motto is "Hard work beats talent, when talent doesn't work hard."... His father suffered a stroke in 2001 and Is involved with the American Stroke Association, with all donations for his funeral in 2014 presented to the ASA...Most memorable sporting event was watching Phil Mickelson's heroic shot from behind the tree on the 13th hole at Augusta National in the 2010 Masters Tournament...Twitter handle is @TJMitchell_.
